Got a blog? Share your blog posts on social networks? Wish comments on those
shared posts also showed up on your blog? Bridgy copies them back for you.

http://brid.gy/

Background: http://snarfed.org/2011-07-27_facebook_app_for_ostatus

IN PROGRESS!


Requires a bunch of libraries because of Google+: google-api-python-client,
httplib2, python-gflags, etc. I'd use git submodules, but I haven't yet found
git repos hosting them. Here are easy setup instructions:

http://code.google.com/p/google-api-python-client/wiki/Installation

Or if you want to download and set them up manually:

# in bridgy source directory
hg clone https://code.google.com/p/google-api-python-client/
ln -s google-api-python-client/apiclient
ln -s google-api-python-client/oauth2client
ln -s google-api-python-client/uritemplate

hg clone https://code.google.com/p/httplib2/
ln -s google-api-python-client/httplib2

svn checkout http://python-gflags.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ python-gflags
ln -s python-gflags/gflags.py 
ln -s python-gflags/gflags_validators.py 


The tests require the App Engine SDK and python-mox.


